The paper focuses on the application of Zero Knowledge Interactive Proofs (ZKIP) on resource constrained devices, which is a topic related to cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of elliptic curve cryptography (ECC), which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed protocols in terms of code size, execution time, message size, and energy requirements, which are topics related to cyber-physical systems (cs.CY), machine learning (cs.LG), and systems and control (cs.SY).
